Package org.point85.uom

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    UnitOfMeasure
    UnitOfMeasure is the interface for a unit of measure.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Conversion
    A Conversion linearly relates an ordinate unit (y) to an abscissa unit (x) by the equation y = ax + b.
    MeasurementSystem
    A MeasurementSystem is a collection of units of measure that have a linear relationship to each other: y = ax + b where x is the unit to be converted, y is the converted unit, a is the scaling factor and b is the offset.
    PowerUOM
    PowerUOM represents a unit of measure with an exponent, for example square metres.
    ProductUOM
    ProductUOM represents a unit of measure that is the product of two other units of measure, for example Newton-metres.
    Quantity
    Quantity represents an amount and UnitOfMeasure.
    QuotientUOM
    QuotientUOM represents a unit of measure that is the ratio of two other units of measure, for example metres per second.
    ScalarUOM
    ScalarUOM represents a simple unit of measure, for example a metre.
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    Unit
    Unit is an enumeration of units of measure types in the International Customary, SI, US and British Imperial systems.
    UnitType
    UnitType is an enumeration of unit of measure types.
